---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { rel, SUPPORT_EMAIL } from '../../consts';
const description = 'Privacy policy for Vibe Rater by Dudley Development.';
---
<Base title="Privacy Policy · Vibe Rater" description={description} path="/privacy/vibe-rater">
  <main class="page">
    <div class="wrap" style="max-width:720px;">
      <a class="back" href={rel('/privacy/')}>← All privacy policies</a>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="updated">Vibe Rater · Last updated June 13, 2026</p>

      <h2>The short version</h2>
      <p>
        Vibe Rater is a free, for-entertainment app supported by ads. The photos you choose are analyzed
        <strong>on your device</strong> and are not uploaded to us or anyone else. We don't run accounts,
        analytics, or trackers of our own, and we never see your photos or personal information. To show ads,
        the app uses Google AdMob, as described below — and you can say no to tracking with one tap.
      </p>

      <h2>Your photos stay on your device</h2>
      <p>
        When you pick or take a photo, Vibe Rater processes it locally on your iPhone to produce its playful
        "vibe" rating. <strong>Your photos are never uploaded, transmitted, or stored on our servers</strong> —
        we have no servers that receive them. The app requests photo-library or camera access only so you can
        choose an image; that access is used on-device and nothing leaves your phone.
      </p>
      <p>
        If a future version of the app ever adds a feature that sends a photo off your device, this policy will
        be updated and that behavior clearly disclosed <em>before</em> it ships.
      </p>

      <h2>What stays on your device</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Your recent results and any saved vibe cards (stored locally so you can revisit them).</li>
        <li>Your sound and haptics preferences.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>This is stored on your device. Uninstalling the app, or clearing history in Settings, removes it.</p>

      <h2>For entertainment only</h2>
      <p>
        Vibe Rater is a novelty. Its scores, grades, and archetypes are meant to be fun and are not a measurement
        of anything real about you, your appearance, or any person in a photo.
      </p>

      <h2>Advertising (Google AdMob)</h2>
      <p>
        The app shows occasional full-screen ads between ratings. Ads are served by <strong>Google AdMob</strong>,
        a third-party advertising network. To serve and measure ads, Google may collect device information such as
        the advertising identifier (IDFA), IP address, and coarse ad-interaction data. We do not receive, store, or
        link any of this to you.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Your choice:</strong> the first time an ad is about to appear, iOS asks whether to allow tracking. If you choose <em>Ask App Not to Track</em>, you still get ads — just non-personalized ones.</li>
        <li><strong>Change your mind anytime:</strong> iOS Settings → Privacy &amp; Security → Tracking → Vibe Rater.</li>
        <li>How Google uses this data is described in <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads">Google's advertising policy</a> and <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy">Google's privacy policy</a>.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Children</h2>
      <p>
        We do not knowingly collect any data from anyone, including children under 13. There are no accounts,
        profiles, or in-app messaging, and the app is not directed at children.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>
        If this policy ever changes materially, the new version will be posted at this URL with an updated date
        above. Continued use of the app after a change constitutes acceptance.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Questions? Email <a href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`}>{SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>
